articles.title: Support for mandatory vaccinations is growing in Canada, poll finds
articles.description: The online survey found that 72 per cent of Canadians think vaccinations for children should "definitely" or "probably" be mandatory in their province.

articles.title: Political parties add clarity and confusion to Calgary municipal election
articles.description: With dozens of candidates, the introduction of party politics, and a sea of colourful candidate signs, deciding who to vote for in Calgary's municipal election is a daunting task.

articles.title: Call of the Wilde: Montreal Canadiens dominate Detroit Red Wings 5-1 in home opener
articles.description: Montreal should not have been the fresher of the two teams, after travelling overnight after their loss to Toronto, but they were. Brian Wilde has more.

articles.title: Edmonton students push to get fellow young voters involved in election
articles.description: The University of Alberta's Students' Union says so far, they're seeing more engagement in this election and the city says it's also seeing a higher turnout at advance voting.

articles.title: MLB announces Blue Jays broadcast schedule
articles.description: The Toronto Blue Jays will open the American League Championship Series with a Sunday night matchup at Rogers Centre.

articles.title: Calgary driver concerned for others after base for traffic post damages his vehicle
articles.description: A Calgary driver is hoping the company responsible for traffic mitigation on Deerfoot Trail will pay to have his car fixed after it was damaged by materials left on the roadway.

articles.title: Another October, another letdown: Yankees eliminated by Blue Jays in ALDS
articles.description: The New York Yankees' season ended with more silence than celebration. In front of a restless crowd at Yankee Stadium, the Toronto Blue Jays closed out the ALDS with a 5-2 win

articles.title: Blue Jays take Game 4 over Yankees to secure first ALCS trip since 2016
articles.description: The Toronto Blue Jays are heading to the ALCS for the first time since 2016 as they took Game 4 of the ALDS from the New York Yankees, 5-2, in the Bronx.

articles.title: Maple Leafs top Canadiens 5-2 to open post-Marner era in Toronto
articles.description: Morgan Rielly scored the winner in the third period and added an assist as the Toronto Maple Leafs topped the Montreal Canadiens 5-2 in the first game of the post-Mitch Marner era Wednesday.

articles.title: Canada's prime minister discussed reviving contentious Keystone XL pipeline with Trump
articles.description: A Canadian government official familiar with the matter says Prime Minister Mark Carney raised the prospect of reviving the contentious Keystone XL pipeline project during his White House meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump this week
